        <h2>Why Choose Java Full Stack Development?</h2>
        <p>Java Full Stack Development allows developers to work on both front-end and back-end technologies, offering a versatile skill set that is highly in demand. Here are some key features of Java Full Stack Development:</p>

        <ul>
            <li><b>Complete Web Application Development:</b> Full stack developers handle both the client-side (UI) and the server-side (backend), making them highly valuable to companies looking for end-to-end solutions.</li>
            <li><b>Strong Back-End Skills:</b> You will learn Java, which powers robust back-end logic with technologies like Spring Boot, Hibernate, and more.</li>
            <li><b>Modern Front-End Frameworks:</b> Java Full Stack developers work with modern front-end technologies such as React, Angular, and Vue.js.</li>
            <li><b>Database Knowledge:</b> Master the use of databases like MySQL, MongoDB, and PostgreSQL to manage data efficiently.</li>
            <li><b>DevOps and Deployment:</b> Full stack developers also work with tools like Docker, Jenkins, and Git for deployment, making it easier to deliver applications at scale.</li>
        </ul>

